

// setting up system property for chrome driver

System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver", "D:\\Trainings\\Testing for Kranthi\\Java Training\\JavaTrainingForKranthi\\With_Java\\BrowserDrivers\\chromedriver.exe");


// initialize chrome driver

WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();

WebDriver : selenium java interface
ChromeDriver : this is a selenium java class implementing WebDriver interface. 

Note : WebDriver's parent interfact is "SearchContext"

SearchContext (I)<<---WebDriver (I)<<--ChromeDriver (C)


// to implement hard wait 


Thread.sleep(wait_time);  // wait_time should be milliseconds


// navigating to URL

driver.get("url"); // url has to be a string


// maximising the window
		
driver.manage().window().maximize();


// close the browser window

driver.close(); 








 